---
/**
 * Realises ADR-0016 (manual content-collection wiring) per ADR-0015.
 * Static page linking to the four IA-spec documents in docs/information-architecture/.
 */
import Layout from '@/layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="Manual — information architecture">
  <h1>Ontology-manual information architecture</h1>

  <p class="lead">
    The four IA-spec documents below govern how the OPDA ontology model is documented.
    They specify the structure, conventions, and audience routing for each tier of the
    <a href="/manual">Ontology manual</a>.
  </p>

  <p>
    These specs are the authoritative source for the documentation structure — not for
    the ontology model itself (which is governed by the
    <a href="/modelling">Modelling section</a> ADRs).
  </p>

  <h2>IA specifications</h2>

  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Tier</th>
        <th>Audience</th>
        <th>IA specification</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td><a href="/manual/concept">Concept</a></td>
        <td>Property-industry SMEs</td>
        <td>
          <a href="/resource.html?path=docs/information-architecture/concept-model-ia.md">
            concept-model-ia.md
          </a>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><a href="/manual/logical">Logical</a></td>
        <td>Data engineers, solution architects</td>
        <td>
          <a href="/resource.html?path=docs/information-architecture/logical-model-ia.md">
            logical-model-ia.md
          </a>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><a href="/manual/physical-database">Physical — deployment</a></td>
        <td>Triplestore operators, SPARQL consumers</td>
        <td>
          <a href="/resource.html?path=docs/information-architecture/physical-database-ia.md">
            physical-database-ia.md
          </a>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><a href="/manual/physical-ontology">Physical — ontology</a></td>
        <td>Ontology engineers, SHACL implementers</td>
        <td>
          <a href="/resource.html?path=docs/information-architecture/physical-ontology-ia.md">
            physical-ontology-ia.md
          </a>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <p>
    The cross-tier traceability requirement (every entity must carry a stable URI resolving
    across all four tiers) is specified in
    <a href="/resource.html?path=docs/information-architecture/README.md">
      docs/information-architecture/README.md
    </a>.
  </p>
</Layout>
